Module AM37
Package it.polimi.ingsw.controller

Class MessageManagerParser

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.controller.MessageManagerParser
All Implemented Interfaces:
ServerMessageManagerVisitor
public class MessageManagerParser
extends java.lang.Object
implements ServerMessageManagerVisitor
Handles incoming messages from the client and their respective responses

In particular, this class' objects handle all the messages regarding the actual game, from the choice of the gods to the winner declaration.
It also provides the only contact point between the game controller and the outside world, via the parseMessageFromServerToClient(Message) method.

  • Constructor Details

    • MessageManagerParser

      public MessageManagerParser​(Lobby lobby)
      Default constructor

      Every Lobby is linked to a parser, which manages the incoming messages from the lobby's users; The serverController has to be set separately, since it can be set up in different moments

      Parameters:
      lobby - the lobby associated to this parser

    • parseMessageFromServerToClient

      public void parseMessageFromServerToClient​(Message message)
      Sends a message

      Since the parser has no reference to the network interface, the message has to be sent to the lobby, which will take care of sending the message, using the Lobby.sendMessage(String, Message) method.

      Parameters:
      message - the message to send

    • cannotHandleMessage

      public void cannotHandleMessage​(Message message)
      Invoked in case the message received has a Visitor method not implemented in this parser. In this case, it has been decided to ignore the message and literally take no action, leading the client to doom.
      Specified by:
      cannotHandleMessage in interface ServerMessageManagerVisitor
      Parameters:
      message - the message to discard
